        <?php echo $this->stencil->setHeadline('RxJava - Reactive Extensions'); ?>
        <p><strong>RxJava</strong> is a <?php echo $this->stencil->addLink('Java', 'L'); ?> VM implementation of <?php echo $this->stencil->addLink('Reactive Extensions', 'L'); ?>, a library for composing asynchronous and event-based programs by using observable sequences.</p>
        <p>It extends the <strong>observer pattern</strong> to support sequences of data / events and adds operators that allow you to compose sequences together declaratively while abstracting away concerns about things like low-level threading, synchronization, thread-safety, concurrent data structures, and non-blocking I/O.</p>
        <p>It supports Java 5 or higher and JVM-based languages such as <?php echo $this->stencil->addLink('Groovy', 'L'); ?>, <?php echo $this->stencil->addLink('Clojure', 'L'); ?>, and <?php echo $this->stencil->addLink('Scala', 'L'); ?>.</p>
